In [[telecommunication]], '''control communications''' is the branch of technology devoted to the design, development, and application of [[telecommunication|communications]] facilities used specifically for control purposes, such as for controlling (a) industrial processes, (b) movement of resources, (c) [[electric power]] generation, distribution, and utilization, (d) communications networks, and (e) transportation systems.

