{{wiktionarypar|silent butler}}
A '''silent butler''', sometimes called an '''ash butler''', is a small container, often of [[base metal]], sometimes silver or silverplate, with a handle and hinged cover, used for collecting ashes or crumbs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.google.com/patents?id=aCxYAAAAEBAJ&pg=PA2&dq=%22silent+butler%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=9fG6T7GBLqGLiAKRrZHVDQ&ved=0CDoQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=%22silent%20butler%22&f=false |title=Patent US2752622 - COMBINED SILENT BUTLER AND CRUMBER - Google Patents |publisher=Google.com |date=1 July 1953 |accessdate=23 March 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.auctionbytes.com/cab/abu/y210/m06/abu0264/s06 |title=Collector's Corner: Silent Butler |publisher=Auctionbytes.com |date= |accessdate=23 March 2013}}</ref> They were more common prior to the modern period, and enjoyed some popularity being made as a home construction project in the US.<ref name="Corporation">{{cite book|title=Popular Science|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hCQDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA166|accessdate=4 August 2013|date=October 1947|publisher=Bonnier Corporation|page=166|issn=0161-7370}}</ref><ref name="Corporation1949">{{cite book|title=Popular Science|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OSQDAAAAMBAJ&pg=RA1-PA178|accessdate=4 August 2013|date=August 1949|publisher=Bonnier Corporation|page=1|issn=0161-7370}}</ref><ref name="Magazines1948">{{cite book|title=Popular Mechanics|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4tgDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA185|accessdate=4 August 2013|date=February 1948|publisher=Hearst Magazines|page=185|issn=0032-4558}}</ref> They are now often considered [[collector's item]]s, or are valued for their [[retro]] appeal.<ref>{{cite web|author=The Peak of Chic |url=http://thepeakofchic.blogspot.com/2009/10/silent-butler-and-some-canapes.html |title=The Peak of Chic®: The Silent Butler and Some Canapes |publisher=Thepeakofchic.blogspot.com |date=8 October 2009 |accessdate=23 March 2013}}</ref>

